<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-01T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="82" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d82">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.943/5: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-01T12:00:00-05:00">April 1,
                                1936—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>70. Reference Dairen’s despatch of February 26 addressed to Embassy at
                                Tokyo<note n="27" xml:id="d82fn27">Not printed.</note> in regard to
                            reported tariff agreement between the authorities of the “autonomous”
                            area of North China and those of Japan.</p>
                        <p>Department assumes that you are already studying the situation under
                            reference and that in due course you will inform the Department of the
                            results of your investigation.<note n="28" xml:id="d82fn28">See telegram
                                No. 215, April 30, 11 a.m., from the Ambassador in China, <ref target="#pg_126">p. 126</ref>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>